ermany national youth football team|Germany U20]] | nationalcaps4= 5  | nationalgoals4= 0\n| club-update   = 16 April 2020\n| ntupdate      = \n}}\n\n'''Matti Steinmann''' (born 8 January 1995) is a Finnish-German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a central [[midfielder]] for [[A-League]] club [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]].<ref name=\"soccerway\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ville-matti-steinmann/254390/|title=Germany - V. Steinmann - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2014-09-20}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Hamburger SV===\nSteinmann is a youth exponent from [[Hamburger SV]]. He made his [[Bundesliga]] debut at 20 September 2014 against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. He replaced [[Nicolai M\u00fcller]] after 87 minutes in a 0-0 home draw.<ref name=\"soccerway2\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/09/20/germany/bundesliga/hamburger-sv/fc-bayern-munchen/1713451/|title=Hamburger SV vs. Bayern M\u00fcnchen - 20 September 2014 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=2014-09-20}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Vendsyssel FF====\nSteinmann was loaned out to [[Danish Superliga]] club [[Vendsyssel FF]] on 31 January 2019 for the rest of the season.<ref>[https://www.vendsysselff.dk/vendsyssel-ff-tilknytter-tysk-midtbanespiller/ VENDSYSSEL FF TILKNYTTER TYSK MIDTBANESPILLER], vendsysselff.dk, 31 January 2019</ref>\n\n===Wellington Phoenix===\nIn August 2019, Steinmann joined [[A-League]] club [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]] on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/a-league/114880169/german-matti-steinmann-bulks-up-wellington-phoenix-midfield|title=German Matti Steinmann strengthens Wellington Phoenix midfield|first=Phillip|last=Rollo|newspaper=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/2013-14/hamburger-sv-12/63955/spieler_steinmann-matti.html kicker profile] {{in lang|de}}\n* {{Soccerway|ville-matti-steinmann/254390}}\n\n{{Wellington Phoenix FC squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Steinmann, Matti}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German people of Finnish descent]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:3. Liga players]]\n[[Category:Hamburger SV players]]\n[[Category:Hamburger SV II players]]\n[[Category:Chemnitzer FC players]]\n[[Category:1. FSV Mainz 05 II players]]\n[[Category:Vendsyssel FF players]]\n[[Category:Wellington Phoenix FC players]]\n[[Category:Danish Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Germany youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Hamburg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Matti Steinmann\n| image       = Matti Steinmann 2018.jpg\n| fullname    = Ville Matti Steinmann\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1995|1|8|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Hamburg]], [[Germany]]\n| height      = {{convert|1.88|m|abbr=on}}\n| position    = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]]\n| clubnumber  = 5\n| youthyears1 =           | youthclubs1 = TSV Bargteheide\n| youthyears2 = 2007\u20132009 | youthclubs2 = SV Preu\u00dfen Reinfeld\n| youthyears3 = 2009\u20132014 | youthclubs3 = [[Hamburger SV]]\n| years1      = 2012\u20132015 | caps1 = 52 | goals1 = 5 | clubs1 = [[Hamburger SV II]]\n| years2      = 2014\u20132016 | caps2 =  1 | goals2 = 0 | clubs2 = [[Hamburger SV]]\n| years3      = 2015\u20132016 | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 1 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Chemnitzer FC]] (loan)\n| years4      = 2016\u20132017 | caps4 = 25 | goals4 = 2 | clubs4 = [[1. FSV Mainz 05 II]]\n| years5      = 2017\u20132019 | caps5 = 24 | goals5 = 2 | clubs5 = [[Hamburger SV II]]\n| years6      = 2018\u20132019 | caps6 =